    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="747"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857Ar1/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Cork</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Report by telegraph brief summary of affidavits in <hi rend="italic">Arabic</hi>
                    case, covering particularly question of warning, ramming, convoy, and whether
                        <hi rend="italic">Arabic</hi> was going to assistance of <hi rend="italic"
                        >Dunsley</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
